@page
@model AboutModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About StudySax";
}

<div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-md-8">

        <h1 class="h2 mb-4">About StudySax</h1>

        <p class="lead">
            StudySax is an interactive sheet music platform that brings expert advice from
            notable saxophonists across the United States directly to your fingertips — without
            breaking the bank.
        </p>

        <p>
            Inspired by apps like ForScore, StudySax goes a step further: as you follow along
            with a score, highlighted sections appear wherever a saxophonist has left a tip or
            insight. Tap any highlight to expand it and read their advice in full — whether it's
            a fingering technique, a phrasing suggestion, or guidance on how to approach a
            particularly tricky passage.
        </p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-5 mb-3">Expert Advice, Right on the Page</h2>
        <p>
            Instead of searching through videos, books, or expensive private lessons, StudySax
            puts curated guidance from accomplished saxophonists exactly where you need it —
            embedded in the music itself. Each highlighted section is tied to the specific
            measure or phrase it applies to, so the advice is always in context.
        </p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-5 mb-3">Built for Students &amp; Audition Prep</h2>
        <p>
            StudySax includes dedicated guidance for auditions, with a particular focus on
            high school audition repertoire. Saxophonists share what they wish they had known,
            giving students a real edge when it matters most.
        </p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-5 mb-3">Efficient. Concise. Affordable.</h2>
        <p>
            Learning from great musicians shouldn't require a fortune. StudySax is designed to
            deliver high-quality, practical advice in a focused and accessible format — so
            students can spend more time playing and less time searching.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 d-flex gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <a asp-page="/Index" class="btn btn-primary">Browse Scores</a>
            <a asp-page="/About/Creator" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Meet the Creator</a>
            <a asp-page="/Contact" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
